commitResults.messageTitle: Renamed all instances of Duke to Alvis. Modified initial greeting and goodbye.
Modified Alvis to repeat user input and terminate if 'bye' is entered
Added ability to store text and display stored text when needed

commitResults.messageBody:
Task is represented as Strings

There are attributes aside from description that is tagged to a task and a string is not able to encapsulate those attributes

Let's create a class called Task, which allows us to associate such attributes to an instance of that object. This allows us to use the Task class as a parent class for various types of tasks that might appear in the future
